ne in the cited sources. Would you like me to search for timeline or ETA details?","bullets":[],"sources":[],"citations":[],"answer_text":"I couldn't find enough grounded evidence yet. Could you narrow this to one area so I can cite it reliably? Could you narrow this to one area so I can cite it reliably?\n\nI couldn't find a specific deadline in the cited sources. Would you like me to search for timeline or ETA details?","sources_used":[],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T07:01:50.544Z"},{"id":"a718d35c-4aad-48d6-9309-3942974191e9","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What are our Q4 OKRs for the AI search project?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:00:32.863Z"},{"id":"942bba44-6371-4ac5-b996-2936df9a79b4","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search by November 15. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms such as Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency goal of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [1][3].\n\n- The target launch date for the semantic search is November 15, 2024, with the project currently in the design review approved stage [3].\n- The system will use a combination of Pinecone for the vector database, OpenAI's text-embedding model for embeddings, and Claude Sonnet 3.5 for answer generation [3][4].\n- The cost estimate for maintaining the infrastructure is approximately $300 per month, with a detailed rollout plan involving internal and limited beta phases before the general availability on November 15 [5].\n\nWant me to pull up details on the rollout phases or the technical architecture?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search by November 15. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms such as Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency goal of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [1][3].\n\n- The target launch date for the semantic search is November 15, 2024, with the project currently in the design review approved stage [3].\n- The system will use a combination of Pinecone for the vector database, OpenAI's text-embedding model for embeddings, and Claude Sonnet 3.5 for answer generation [3][4].\n- The cost estimate for maintaining the infrastructure is approximately $300 per month, with a detailed rollout plan involving internal and limited beta phases before the general availability on November 15 [5].\n\nWant me to pull up details on the rollout phases or the technical architecture?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search by November 15. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms such as Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency goal of under 2 seconds for the 95th percentile of queries [1][3].\n\n- The target launch date for the semantic search is November 15, 2024, with the project currently in the design review approved stage [3].\n- The system will use a combination of Pinecone for the vector database, OpenAI's text-embedding model for embeddings, and Claude Sonnet 3.5 for answer generation [3][4].\n- The cost estimate for maintaining the infrastructure is approximately $300 per month, with a detailed rollout plan involving internal and limited beta phases before the general availability on November 15 [5].\n\nWant me to pull up details on the rollout phases or the technical architecture?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:00:41.809Z"},{"id":"bd90a661-b471-4ec5-b6dc-a6a956d8b72c","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"Are there any blockers for the AI search launch?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T09:00:55.258Z"},{"id":"4ea6d5dd-358e-45a7-ade5-c2cd113a06dd","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team has requested an increase in the quota for EC2 instances in the eu-west-1 region, which is crucial for deploying the Pinecone vector database needed to serve European customers. - Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n\n- Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n- If the quota increase is not approved in time, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which will only support 100,000 daily active users instead of the planned 200,000 [12][24].\n- The escalation status is critical, and the team has already escalated the issue to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if necessary [14][22].\n- This blocker poses a high business impact, potentially affecting $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from signed contracts with European enterprise customers [24].\n\nWould you like me to provide more details on the mitigation plan or the escalation process?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team has requested an increase in the quota for EC2 instances in the eu-west-1 region, which is crucial for deploying the Pinecone vector database needed to serve European customers. - Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n\n- Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n- If the quota increase is not approved in time, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which will only support 100,000 daily active users instead of the planned 200,000 [12][24].\n- The escalation status is critical, and the team has already escalated the issue to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if necessary [14][22].\n- This blocker poses a high business impact, potentially affecting $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from signed contracts with European enterprise customers [24].\n\nWould you like me to provide more details on the mitigation plan or the escalation process?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Yes, there is a significant blocker for the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team has requested an increase in the quota for EC2 instances in the eu-west-1 region, which is crucial for deploying the Pinecone vector database needed to serve European customers. - Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n\n- Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving this issue, with a deadline of November 11, just a few days before the planned launch on November 15 [12][24].\n- If the quota increase is not approved in time, there is a fallback plan to deploy with 50 instances, which will only support 100,000 daily active users instead of the planned 200,000 [12][24].\n- The escalation status is critical, and the team has already escalated the issue to the AWS VP level, with an executive call scheduled for November 1 if necessary [14][22].\n- This blocker poses a high business impact, potentially affecting $500,000 in annual recurring revenue from signed contracts with European enterprise customers [24].\n\nWould you like me to provide more details on the mitigation plan or the escalation process?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Tea