 Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency of under 2 seconds for 95% of queries [1][3].\n\nWould you like more details on specific metrics or other project-related objectives?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The Q4 Objectives and Key Results (OKRs) for the AI search project include launching the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search system with a new semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The goal is to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency of under 2 seconds for 95% of queries [1][3].\n\n- This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search system with a new semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. [1]\n- The goal is to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency of under 2 seconds for 95% of queries [1][3].\n\nWould you like more details on specific metrics or other project-related objectives?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"The Q4 Objectives and Key Results (OKRs) for the AI search project include launching the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search system with a new semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The goal is to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency of under 2 seconds for 95% of queries [1][3].\n\n- This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search system with a new semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. [1]\n- The goal is to index over 500,000 documents across various platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a latency of under 2 seconds for 95% of queries [1][3].\n\nWould you like more details on specific metrics or other project-related objectives?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:25.089Z"},{"id":"35e20d6a-a4ab-4a02-8aab-5fca33f93c4e","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves transitioning from a keyword-based search to a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a target latency of under two seconds for the 95th percentile.\n\n- The key objective is to launch the semantic search by November 15, 2024, which is crucial for meeting the project's goals [3][5].\n- A successful launch will require validating system performance through internal and limited beta testing phases, with a general availability rollout planned for mid-November [5].\n- The project involves significant engineering efforts to ensure compliance with data residency requirements and high system availability, specifically for European customers due to GDPR requirements [6][8].\n\nWould you like more details on the metrics used to measure the success of these OKRs, or on any specific technical components?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves transitioning from a keyword-based search to a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a target latency of under two seconds for the 95th percentile.\n\n- The key objective is to launch the semantic search by November 15, 2024, which is crucial for meeting the project's goals [3][5].\n- A successful launch will require validating system performance through internal and limited beta testing phases, with a general availability rollout planned for mid-November [5].\n- The project involves significant engineering efforts to ensure compliance with data residency requirements and high system availability, specifically for European customers due to GDPR requirements [6][8].\n\nWould you like more details on the metrics used to measure the success of these OKRs, or on any specific technical components?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"The Q4 OKRs for the AI search project include launching the semantic search feature by November 15, 2024. This involves transitioning from a keyword-based search to a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The project aims to index over 500,000 documents across platforms like Google Drive, Confluence, Slack, and Jira, enabling natural language queries with a target latency of under two seconds for the 95th percentile.\n\n- The key objective is to launch the semantic search by November 15, 2024, which is crucial for meeting the project's goals [3][5].\n- A successful launch will require validating system performance through internal and limited beta testing phases, with a general availability rollout planned for mid-November [5].\n- The project involves significant engineering efforts to ensure compliance with data residency requirements and high system availability, specifically for European customers due to GDPR requirements [6][8].\n\nWould you like more details on the metrics used to measure the success of these OKRs, or on any specific technical components?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9