-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"keyFacts":[],"answer_text":"This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. The goal is to enable natural language queries with a latency of less than 2 seconds for 95% of queries. - This involves replacing the existing keyword-based search with a more advanced semantic search powered by vector embeddings and large language models. [1]\n- The goal is to enable natural language queries with a latency of less than 2 seconds for 95% of queries. [1]\n\n[1]\n\nWould you like me to go deeper on timeline, owners, or risks?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"relatedSources":[],"citationIndexMap":{"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e":1},"needsClarification":true,"clarifyingQuestions":["Would you like more details on the specific metrics or any potential risks associated with these OKRs?"]}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:38.601Z"},{"id":"ce832ad4-2746-4f7e-8b51-2829e8195f7f","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"Are there any blockers for the AI search launch?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:50.018Z"},{"id":"847494d9-cdd1-4310-8fb1-7694c9c506d4","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Yes, there is a critical blocker affecting the AI search launch related to the AWS EU region quota. The team is currently facing a delay in receiving a quota increase for the eu-west-1 region, which is essential for deploying the AI search feature to European customers. This blocker is managed by Jordan Martinez, and there is a hard deadline of November 11 to resolve the issue, as it impacts the November 15 launch date.\n\n- The AWS EU region quota blocker is the most significant risk to the launch. It prevents deploying the necessary infrastructure to support European customers at scale [12][24].\n- Jordan Martinez is leading the efforts to resolve this issue, with daily check-ins and an executive escalation planned if the quota is not approved by November 1 [12][17].\n- The business impact includes a potential $500K ARR at risk from signed contracts with EU enterprise customers like Siemens, Volkswagen, and BNP Paribas [24].\n- A fallback plan involves deploying with reduced capacity (50 instances instead of 100), which would support only 100K daily active users instead of the targeted 200K [24].\n\nWould you like me to pull up more details on the mitigation strategies or the escalation timeline?","sources_used":[{"id":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1OaWf-KzyUEnNp_aUm9dGc9g9scyr-x0n/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"AI_Search_Architecture.pdf","sourceId":"82b9fe07-ba26-415c-82ca-41614f25977e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1cWDQ4mEaj5ym2QFicMP-AEp4v9yg2qMK/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Engineering_AllHands_Oct28_2024.pdf","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-z6r1IrvdWltGMYOjsUlg6t7A9WU6xt_/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Product_Roadmap_2025.pdf","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1blwqBYR0kIAz8lgFDkzo6uRQBs0Vkkks/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Q4_2024_OKRs.pdf","sourceId":"96677b12-e487-41e8-b321-e696e442eaa2","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"},{"id":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MHcvhX7gaYOpy4WPPfr8CXtrPKr1RxBJ/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"Team_Quick_Reference_Guide.pdf","sourceId":"48f70248-463f-42cc-9296-330711b86ac3","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:36:57.172Z"},{"id":"1f4cbbe3-74c8-4a54-af12-5f97052cc14b","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What vector database are we using and why?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:37:09.455Z"},{"id":"715a6911-0e7a-4a11-90b3-0048335c1e3d","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Hello! How can I help you today?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Hello! How can I help you today?","sources":[],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Hello! How can I help you today?","quickReplies":[{"text":"What are our Q4 OKRs for the AI search project?","label":"What are our Q4 OKRs?"},{"text":"Are there any blockers for the AI search launch?","label":"Any blockers?"},{"text":"What's our 2025 product roadmap?","label":"What's our roadmap?"},{"text":"Who should I contact about infrastructure issues?","label":"Who handles infrastructure?"}],"sources_used":[]}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:37:09.464Z"},{"id":"6c743954-69a7-4b09-a427-ee5cc47d3567","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"Who is responsible for fixing the AWS blocker and when is the deadline?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:37:22.709Z"},{"id":"613f05cf-e433-46a4-bb00-fce67bd5ea5e","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving the AWS EU region quota blocker. - Jordan Martinez, the Infrastructure Lead, is managing the resolution of this blocker and is conducting daily check-ins with AWS. - The blocker poses a significant risk to the launch, impacting the ability to serve European customers and potentially affecting $500K in annual recurring revenue from key contracts. Would you like more information on the escalation process or the fallback plans in place?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving the AWS EU region quota blocker. - Jordan Martinez, the Infrastructure Lead, is managing the resolution of this blocker and is conducting daily check-ins with AWS. - The blocker poses a significant risk to the launch, impacting the ability to serve European customers and potentially affecting $500K in annual recurring revenue from key contracts. Would you like more information on the escalation process or the fallback plans in place?","bullets":[],"sources":[{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citations":[],"answer_text":"Jordan Martinez is responsible for resolving the AWS EU region quota blocker. - Jordan Martinez, the Infrastructure Lead, is managing the resolution of this blocker and is conducting daily check-ins with AWS. - The blocker poses a significant risk to the launch, impacting the ability to serve European customers and potentially affecting $500K in annual recurring revenue from key contracts. Would you like more information on the escalation process or the fallback plans in place?","sources_used":[{"id":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","url":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pcwDpaqMVClET6mfadGy_oCYn4FgigJ-/view?usp=drivesdk","title":"JIRA_INFRA-1247_AWS_EU_Blocker.pdf","sourceId":"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f","sourceType":"drive","sourceTypeLabel":"Drive"}],"citationIndexMap":{"f7ada39b-e572-498c-8197-736a9a21f56f":1}}},"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:37:43.123Z"},{"id":"7d618734-072b-426f-8d60-1d783005b7c2","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What's our 2025 product roadmap?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:37:54.226Z"},{"id":"fa61eb81-d967-40d1-98ac-6c347f394c8e","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"user","content":"What's our 2025 product roadmap?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":null,"metadataJson":null,"createdAt":"2026-02-24T13:38:24.235Z"},{"id":"d9c38dd2-10a4-4767-9d10-4da897ea550b","conversationId":"706ca2da-55d9-4479-8b95-eb8218d4a035","role":"assistant","content":"The 2025 product roadmap for FieldCopilot is focused on expanding user base and enhancing customer satisfaction through various strategic initiatives. The overarching goal is to grow from 50,000 to 500,000 users while maintaining a customer satisfaction rate of over 95%. The roadmap is structured around key themes and priorities for each quarter. - In Q1 2025, the focus will be on polishing the product and improving performance, with a specific initiative to implement multi-tenancy for enterprise customers. [2]\n- In Q3 2025, the focus will be on integration with Microsoft 365 to improve search capabilities and unlock enterprise prospects. [2]\n\nWould you like me to go deeper on timeline, owners, or risks?","toolCallId":null,"citationsJson":[{"charEnd":5170,"chunkId":"c689b21c-5a11-47c1-8297-34af3c879e59","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","charStart":4170,"sourceVersionId":"50e10024-f71d-4d49-ab5e-076e1e541a0c"},{"charEnd":1850,"chunkId":"cdfbfbef-a4af-4847-adc5-690b5e1c62c6","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","charStart":850,"sourceVersionId":"d7444374-86d6-4ede-acf8-c1267f70328e"},{"charEnd":4298,"chunkId":"60bf048d-8963-452f-9312-f87ba87cec3a","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","charStart":3298,"sourceVersionId":"d7444374-86d6-4ede-acf8-c1267f70328e"},{"charEnd":5969,"chunkId":"d022f79c-eff8-4412-ab33-3f46479b3888","sourceId":"1602cb5c-021a-4f74-9abc-944fbb22c19e","charStart":4998,"sourceVersionId":"d7444374-86d6-4ede-acf8-c1267f70328e"}],"metadataJson":{"response":{"answer":"The 2025 product roadmap for FieldCopilot is focused on expanding user base and enhancing customer satisfaction through various strategic initiatives. The overarching goal is to grow from 50,000 to 500,000 users while maintaining a customer satisfaction rate of over 95%. The roadmap is structured around key themes and priorities for each quarter. - In Q1 2025, the focus will be on polishing the product and improving performance, with a specific initiative to implement multi-tenancy for enterprise customers. [2]\n- In Q3 2025, the focus will be on integration with Microsoft 365 to improve search capabilities and unlock enterprise prospects. [2]\n\nWould you like me to go deeper on timeline, owners, or risks?","bullets":[{"claim":"In Q1 2025, the focus will be on polishing the product and improving performance, with a specific initiative to implement multi-tenancy for enterprise customers.","citations":[{"charEnd":5170,"chunkId":"c689b21c-5a11-47c1-8297-34af3c879e59","sourceId":"d4da6b5b-9916-46cd-ac80-3ae9bc780f71","charStart":4170,"sourceVersionId":"50e10024-f71d-4d49-ab5e-076e1e541a0c"}]},{"claim":"Q2 2025 will introduce real-time sync capabilities to enhance user experience by reducing latency.","citations":[{"char